President Trump held a roundtable discussion on the issue of MS-13, a violent gang that has been causing havoc in communities across the United States. The President and various officials discussed the need for stronger immigration laws, as many MS-13 members enter the country illegally and exploit loopholes in the system. Families who have lost loved ones to MS-13 violence also shared their stories and expressed the need for action to be taken against the gang. The President emphasized the importance of tackling MS-13 and expressed his commitment to eradicating the gang from American communities.